<%- layout("layouts/boilerplate") %>

<div class="find-cohost-page">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-section">
      <h1>Find a co-host</h1>
      <p class="lead">Partner with a co-host to manage your listing together</p>
      <p>Co-hosts on the Co-Host Network typically have high ratings, low cancellation rates and established Wanderlust hosting experience.</p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Find a co-host</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8">
        <h2>What is a co-host?</h2>
        <p>A co-host is someone you invite to help manage your listing. They can handle day-to-day tasks like communicating with guests, managing bookings, and coordinating cleanings, while you remain the primary host.</p>

        <h2>What co-hosts can do</h2>
        <div class="cohost-tasks">
          <div class="task-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-comments"></i> Guest communication</h3>
            <p>Respond to inquiries, send check-in instructions, and communicate with guests throughout their stay.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="task-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-calendar-alt"></i> Calendar management</h3>
            <p>Update availability, block dates, and manage bookings on your calendar.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="task-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-broom"></i> Cleaning coordination</h3>
            <p>Schedule cleanings between stays and ensure the space is ready for guests.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="task-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-key"></i> Check-in and check-out</h3>
            <p>Handle guest arrivals and departures, including key exchanges and walkthroughs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="task-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Maintenance coordination</h3>
            <p>Arrange repairs and handle maintenance issues as they arise.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="task-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-star"></i> Review management</h3>
            <p>Respond to guest reviews and encourage guests to leave feedback.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Why get a co-host?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Save time:</strong> Delegate day-to-day tasks so you can focus on other priorities</li>
          <li><strong>Grow your business:</strong> Scale to multiple properties with help managing them</li>
          <li><strong>Expertise:</strong> Partner with experienced hosts who know the platform well</li>
          <li><strong>Flexibility:</strong> Host even when you're traveling or busy with other commitments</li>
          <li><strong>Better guest experience:</strong> Provide 24/7 support to your guests</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to find a co-host</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Search the Co-Host Network:</strong> Browse qualified co-hosts in your area</li>
          <li><strong>Review profiles:</strong> Check ratings, experience, and specializations</li>
          <li><strong>Send requests:</strong> Reach out to co-hosts you're interested in</li>
          <li><strong>Discuss terms:</strong> Agree on responsibilities and compensation</li>
          <li><strong>Add them to your listing:</strong> Invite them as a co-host through your account</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Co-host compensation</h2>
        <p>Co-hosts typically charge a percentage of each booking, usually between 10-25% depending on the services provided. You can negotiate the rate and payment terms directly with your co-host.</p>

        <h2>Things to consider</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Clear communication about expectations and responsibilities</li>
          <li>Written agreement about compensation and payment terms</li>
          <li>Access to your listing and property</li>
          <li>Backup plans for when your co-host is unavailable</li>
          <li>Regular check-ins to ensure everything is running smoothly</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Already know someone?</h2>
        <p>You can invite anyone to be your co-host, not just people from the Co-Host Network. Friends, family members, or trusted neighbors can all become co-hosts on your listing.</p>
        <a href="#" class="btn-link">Invite someone you know →</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <h3>Ready to find a co-host?</h3>
          <p>Browse qualified co-hosts in your area and find the perfect match for your listing.</p>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-block">Search co-hosts</a>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card mt-4">
          <h3>Co-Host Network</h3>
          <p>Our co-hosts are vetted for experience and reliability.</p>
          <ul class="sidebar-links">
            <li><a href="#">View co-host requirements</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Become a co-host</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card mt-4">
          <h3>Hosting resources</h3>
          <ul class="sidebar-links">
            <li><a href="/hosting-resources">Resource Center</a></li>
            <li><a href="/community-forum">Community forum</a></li>
            <li><a href="/hosting-responsibly">Hosting responsibly</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card mt-4">
          <h3>Need help?</h3>
          <p>Our support team can help you with co-host setup and management.</p>
          <a href="/helpcenter" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-block">Contact Support</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
